## 6. src/app/api/v1/script-auth/route.ts (FULL)
The **authentication + payload delivery endpoint**. Handles GET (query) and POST (JSON body). Key logic:

```ts
import { NextResponse } from "next/server";
import { db } from "@/lib/db";
import { rateLimit, getRateLimitHeaders } from "@/lib/rate-limit";
import { decryptObject, hashString, hashToken, randomToken } from "@/lib/crypto";
import { obfuscateLua, isLoadStringPayload } from "@/lib/obfuscator";
import { getClientIp, hashIdentifier } from "@/lib/http";
import { recordSecurityFailure } from "@/lib/ip-reputation";
import { sendDiscordLog } from "@/lib/discord-logger";

// In-memory stores (cleared on restart) — NOT shared across instances!
const sessionTokens = new Map<string, { keyHash; ip; hwid; expires }>();
const keyAttempts = new Map<string, { count; firstAttempt }>();
const recentNonces = new Map<string, number>();
const activeSessions = new Map<string, string>(); // keyHash -> sessionId

// errorResponse -> "ERROR: <msg>" plain text
// getSafeIp: trusts FIRST x-forwarded-for IP only (validates IPv4 regex)
// cleanExpiredStores: sessionTokens 5min, keyAttempts 1hr, nonces 5min, activeSessions 2min

// handleAuth flow:
//   1. rateLimit("script-auth:<ip>", 10, 5min) — 429 if exceeded
//   2. IP reputation check: db.ipReputation.blocked -> 403 (auto-unblock after 30min)
//   3. Parse key/hwid/scriptId/nonce/timestamp/executor/token/check from query OR JSON body
//   4. Replay protection: if nonce seen -> "Replay detected"; timestamp must be within 5min
//   5. Find script; if DISABLED -> 403
//   6. If PUBLIC (keyless): decrypt content, obfuscate if not already a FireLabPayload, return it
//   7. Per-key rate limit: 5 failed attempts/hr -> 429 + KEY_BRUTE_FORCE security failure
//   8. If check=1 & token: validate sessionTokens entry; verify keyHash+hwid match; if IP differs
//      -> CONCURRENT_SESSION (key shared); refresh session; return "OK"
//   9. Find license by keyHash (include script.protectionProfile + hwids)
//  10. If license.scriptId !== scriptId -> INVALID_LICENSE_OR_SCRIPT_BINDING
//  11. Auto-redeem UNREDEEMED on first use (sets ACTIVE, redeemedBy=hwid, computes expiresAt)
//  12. Status checks: SUSPENDED->403, BLACKLISTED->403, EXPIRED->403 (auto-marks EXPIRED)
//  13. HWID lock: auto-bind on first use; if hwidRecord missing & existing hwids -> HWID_MISMATCH
//  14. Concurrent session: if activeSessions has keyHash with different IP+hwid -> 401
//  15. On success: clear keyAttempts, create Activation record, log AUTH_SUCCESS, Discord log,
//      issue sessionToken (randomToken(24), 5min TTL), store in sessionTokens+activeSessions
//  16. Decrypt script.contentEncrypted -> {key}; obfuscate if not FireLabPayload
//  17. Return: payload + "\n--FL:" + sessionToken  (session token appended as Lua comment)
```
**CONCERNS:** (1) In-memory session/nonce/attempt stores are per-instance — with multiple replicas (Railway scaling) a key could be used from 2 IPs hitting different instances, bypassing concurrent-session detection. (2) `recordSecurityFailure` is called on the SAME IP that's attacking — fine. (3) The session token is returned appended to the payload as a Lua comment `--FL:<token>` — visible to the executor/user, though it's a one-time token. (4) HWID = sha256 of the raw hwid string from the executor (`hashIdentifier`/`hashString`).

